      "writtenOn": "2020-01-03T00:22:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "yes. The principle you are implying is \"a function should either return all errors with appstatus, or all without\", but this means a func MUST know if all the funcs it calls return errors with appstatus and, potentially wrap with appstatus. I think it gets fragile quickly. The point of appstatus is  that pieces of code-that-really-understand-what\u0027s-going-on attach appstatus and everything else is an internal error.",
      "parentUuid": "c060208b_28d65cf8",
